Hello! First of all, thanks a lot for the amazing Atom text editor.

I am trying to edit MAGMA files with syntax highlighting and have found the problem below. Steps do reproduce:
1. Convert https://github.com/dhowden/Magma.tmbundle and install the resulting package with the apm utility.
2. Open the MAGMA file below.
3. Switch to Magma with Ctrl+Shift+L.

```
m := 251;
conv := function(x)
    s := Sprintf("%h", Seqint([Integers() ! l : l in Eltseq(x)], 2));
    s := Substring(s, 3, #s-2);
    return "0x" * ("0"^(Ceiling(m/4)-#s)) * s;
end function;

PP<t> := PolynomialRing(GF(2));
Fq<T> := ext<GF(2) | t^251 + t^243 + t^229 + t^211 + 1>;

B := 1;
repeat
    a := 1;
    B := B + 1;
    s := IntegerToSequence(B, 2);
    b := 0;
    for i:=#s to 1 by -1 do
        b := b*t + s[i];
    end for;
    print b;
    E := EllipticCurve([Fq|1,1,0,0,b]);
    print E;
    n := Order(E);
until IsPrime(n) or (IsPrime(n div 4) and (n mod 4 eq 0)) or (IsPrime(n div 2) and (n mod 2 eq 0));
print Factorization(n);

P := 2*Random(E);
conv(P[1]);
conv(P[2]);
```

Thanks a lot!

